content.detailedDescription: My son and i were heading home in our car around 8 at night & we noticed 4 bright objects in the sky & not moving. then 2 disappeared. then the two that were left seemed to hover & then one of the objects pulsated quickly as it dropped closer to the other object. i have never seen anything like this before. no of the objects made noise. the two objects seemed to be communicating with one another by pulsating. then the one object started to rise. that is when i stopped filming because we had to move out of the way for another car.
content.summary: 4 glowing objects that hovered with no sound. then went down to two with one of them pulsating rapidly & descending . then the two seemed to be communicating with each other by pulsating.

content.detailedDescription: I was outside admiring the incredibly bright night sky in rural australia near the township of kingaroy with one other person. we observed many unusual orb like object darting across the sky which started our intregue with the night sky last night.  some were meteorites yet others were different altogether. i was standing facing north next to another individual when a strange feeling came over me that caused me to look back over my right shoulder and upward to the south east direction. i noted a large high altitude object that moved incredibly slow.  unless you watched it it looked stationary but using line of sight and landmarks determined the object to be moving from the north in a southerly direction.  we watched it for a little over 10 mins as it headed south past power lines, edge of roof of house, and over the bunya mountain region.  earlier we had commercial jets head north west to north queensland yet this object was much higher and much much larger than those planes we had seen earlier. my colleague also watched this massive object move so slowly until it disappeared in the south to the east of the bunya mountains. i was amazed and could not speak during the event out of shock and excitement at what we saw.  this was larger than a city and can only be described as a massive mother ship in a typical cigar design. we saw the object disappear into the southern horizon around 2:26am.  i have never seen anything like it before and for hours after all i could say was "fu$k wow".  i just couldnt say anything else out of shock.  the massive cigar object had a bright light at either end and between was the dark shape of the body of the 'vehicle' (if thats the right word to use).  we have talked about it all day today and just cant get it off our minds.  we continue to stay watching the night sky until 4am.  we saw one other object which repeatedly came out of nowhere with massive bright light and then a swift darting back and forth to the same locations.  this final event was just prior to 4am.
content.summary: Giant cigar mother ship - massive

content.detailedDescription: Looked out window at 5:30am & saw a large bright star-like light in the distance above neighbors roof line.  at first thought it was a plane or an asteroid but it continued to travel east towards my house.  it came closer and was a large shining light.  it then hovered for a few minutes and then ascended vertically into the night sky.  i was perplexed & shocked to say the least!  of course i did not grab my camera!

content.detailedDescription: My fiance and i were at a gas station putting gas in. i was sitting in the van looking at the stars because its was a clear night. out of nowhere 3 bright orange looking fire balls appeared out of nowhere. my first thought was we were being under attack. sounds funny but you never know now adays how thing have been. but when i notice the objects flying slow, i got out the van and took a picture. my fiance noticed them right away too. i kept looking at the sky and the guy next to us and hid wife were stund. the mans wife then noticed a forth one following the othere three not to far behind. as we were watching them fly slowly away, they were diappearing one by one. we all couldn't think what just had happened. i was really never a believer of ufos, until that night. i have done researched about ufos since then and from what i saw that night other people as well have. thats a night i will never forget.
content.summary: Four bright orange lying objects.

content.detailedDescription: Brightly glowing orbs in sky around cellphone towers, will appear and are large in comparison to tower from my home approx 10 miles away.  will vanish in a second after getting much brighter. reappears miles away and mimics the same behavior. almost nightly appearances. there was one  night that an orb had given birth to another and absorbed the 2nd back in, i have only witnessed this occurance once with my son.  there are 11 cellphone towers visable from my back door (and i have terrible reception) i am on a slight hill and have great view of everything around me. i have tried to view these objects thru a telescope and binoculers or take a piture and for some reason they are not visable thru these devices.  i have nothing but frustration for these things...But total fascination at the same time.
content.summary: Brightly glowing orbs in sky around cellphone tower..Will appear and are large in comparison to tower from my home.  will vanish in a second after getting brighter. reappears miles away and mimics the same behavior. almost nightly appearances.

content.detailedDescription:
Out on my back lower deck at 3:00 a.M. noticed brilliant white dome shaped light at base of 2/3 trees - about 4 ft wide and 3-4 feet high at ground level. soft but brilliant glow. i looked up at sky (thinking it could be moon light) when i looked back down the light slowly diminished into the ground at the base of 2-3 trees with trunks close together. it maintained it's dome shape while sinking into the ground. the light was very bright white with a sort of blue overtone (like those high speed car head lights).

right after the light disappeared underground, a super bright white beam shown through my back fence and traveled along the fence line until it was just about in front of the trees where the dome shaped light disappeared. at that point, the beam light disappeared as well. my fence is not solid, theres a plank in front and then a plank in back and so on. sort of slatted. i thought perhaps a car was backing out of it's driveway and reflected onto the fence, but i'm in the end unit of 6 townhouses and there's no break for light to shine from the front.  the light beam appeared to be about 10 inches in length and moved slowly the length of the fence line (about24 feet).

at first i thought it came from above (the dome shaped light) and looked for the moon. when i was convinced there was nothing above to generate the light i fixated on, it and it immediately began to "withdraw" into the ground. it disappeared slowly - but maintained an even rate of descent. the edge of the light dome remained "fuzzy" until it disappeared. i remember saying out loud "what the hell is that?" 

when the vertical beamed light shown on the fence line and traveled from one end of my fence line to the other i became quite nervous. it moved almost as slow at the dome light withdrew. i glanced at the back of my house expecting to see a continuation of the beam reflected, but there was no light on the house or on the lawn. the beam through the fence was only about 2 feet off the ground level.

once the beam disappeared my heart was racing - i could hear nothing at all...But went back inside the house. i did notice when i first went out on the deck how incredibly silent it was out there. normally i'd hear night noises (critters etc) - but it was dead silent.

photos attached show trees there dome light was (from ground level to about 4 ft tall) and fence that beam shown "on" or "thru"
content.summary: Bright dome shaped light hovers between trees then descended under ground - with beam

content.detailedDescription: A flash thunderstorm came through on a warm night. it was unexpected. the rain became heavy and i went outside to stand in the rain (being 32 degrees celsius at 8pm at night) - the rain eased but there was still a lot of lightening in the area. i looked to the south and saw red (and few white) lights flashing in a very random order. however, as random as they were, never deviated from a disk orientation. at first (as crazy as this is) i thought they must have been christmas lights on someone's roof antenna. but then realised who i the hell would do that, and b) i've never seen them before (as i frequent my backyard at night). as i slowly begun to realise that what i was witnessing was a ufo, i grabbed my iphone camera and started filming. it caught nothing, as by that time the lights were few and far between and (i guess) so far away the camera couldn't pick them up. the lights slowly just disappeared one by one, until none at all.  - i drove to the beach (2 mins away) to see if they'd reappear, but they didn't. - i have no explanation as to what those lights were. they definitely were not planes or helicopters. i know that for a fact. nor we're they flares (being a boatie). it's all happened in the rockingham / safety bay area during a flash storm.
content.summary: Random flashing lights clearly outlining a disk shaped object

content.detailedDescription: Working outside in a lumber yard, sunny day, i looked up at the moon which was visible to the east when i saw a shiny sphere cruzing in a strait line above the auburn airport going from north to south at a steady speed id say around 150 mph judgeing by the speeds i watch the airplanes use every day while landing and leaving the airport. i tried to get a coworkers attention but he wasnt paying attention, so i watched the object fly further south toward the town of sumner until it faded from view in under a minute. id say this object was kinda small, under the size of a car and around 3 or 4 hundred ft. in the air. looked like the sun was shinning off the object whick looked like reflective silver, when i first saw it i imediatley thought ufo or somekind of new drone but saw no moving parts.
content.summary: Sphere moving steady from north to south

content.detailedDescription: from 2001 to 2004 i lived on the sc ind.Res. nm which is 10 miles ne of los alamos nat.Lab. i'm an artist and love to take pics of wonderful cloud formations, so at sunset i sat outside w my camera, looking west.  1st i saw a jet(w the usual exhaust-trail) heading from n.To w., passing thru 2 separate clouds, at about 25,000 feet. after it disappeared from view here comes another shiny object(from same direction) and it enters cloud #1, but it never came out/passed thru the 1st cloud!! (it somehow stayed in/behind the cloud.) and it dawned on me: there was no ex.Trail accompanying it! i sat transfixed and in about 2 min. it suddenly re-appeared and sped-away much faster than it had arrived, in the same direction it had come from... sure wish i'd had a video camera instead of an slr.
content.summary: Streaking object with no jet trail!!

content.detailedDescription:
Me and 3 friends where driving on a highway in northern oklahoma.  we saw lights and thought it was a low flying airplane and then the craft appeared to the left side of the highway.  the craft was moving nw at a slow speed, it had very bright lights shinning from the bottom of the craft, lighting the ground, it followed the river channel for about 3/4 of a mile and landed.  we where very surprised, we stopped the car and got out to have a better look but the craft had gone behind a hill and landed but we could still see the lights.  could not get anyone to go to the landing sight with me.  me and the other guy went to the local police station but they just laughed at us and told us to go home.

this is the second sighting i had.  i was driving home from work at about 2.00am in the fall of 1973.  i saw a bright light off to the right of the road in the woods.  it was a peach-pink color and a block of light (not a beam) i stopped the van and looked into the woods thinking it was coon hunters.  i set there for a few minutes and then i could see a figure going away from me.  the figure had bright red uniform and knee high blue boots (ha ha) but true.  the figure was gray in color but average size man.  he turned and looked at me, had a high brow ridge, strong jaw, flattend nose and small mouth. he went in a eastery direction and the block of light went with him.  he was less than 50 feet from me when i first saw him.  i have more details but need to tell it to a person.  a few month later my wife was watching johnny carson and there was a man on the show that had sketches of the same figure i had described to her.

this is something i know was real and have lived with for many years.
i have one more sighting but will not go into it now....Seeing object in the sky..Seen by me and my wife.  sincerely  larry d. pierce
content.summary: Driving down highway...At night...4 persons in car

lights were not blinking, and no sound was heard. speed felt fairly slow... the triangle shape remain steady throughout the observation until i lost visibility behind a tree and house.

it was striking weird to all people around me who witness this (about 6 person)

first thing that came to mind was 3 planes in formation, but the color of the light and the fact that no sound could be heard was rather strange.

see link for video i shot with my phone.
content.summary: Yellow triangle shape lights over plano tx

content.detailedDescription:
I woke up at at 1:01 am to go to the bathroom, i then walked to the window and my windows face manhattan, my view is from pelham bay in the bronx. i always have a habit of looking out the window in the early morning hours. i noticed a star like flashing object emitting green, yellow, white, with a what appeared to be a huge red light tip of the craft. i could see it blinking, so i got my nikon sport optics binoculars and it let me see the object a little clearer, at times it appeared disc shaped oval, at times it appeared to be triangular. it stayed in the same position from 1:03 am to 1:29 am. it appeared to have a tip with a large red beam of light, then the other lights seem to be pulsating around it yellow, green, blueish white, it stayed in the same spot, i thought it could be a star, but i live on the 5th floor so i looked at the other stars around an they all appear to reflect a blueish light, but this object kept reflecting different colored lights, with the red point being the most bright. so i went out into the fire escape to get a better view, and there it was, still stationary and hovering, and flashing its colors. it began to very slowly head towards manhattan, but i could still see it with me binoculars. i felt it did not belong to this world, that is the feeling i kept feeling inside. i was not excited, i felt myself asking myself what do you want, why are you here...Kind of questions. 
i noticed at times, the red beam of light grew in intensity, round, very bright. at times the object appeared to be spinning, then for some reason it looked like a rectangular shaped object when the red beam became brighter. i went back inside got a pen and pad, and a heavier coat i was freezing, then went back outside to look and in that one min it just disappeared at 1:29 am,
content.summary: At about 1:03 am i saw what appeaered to be a star like object emiting light

content.detailedDescription: At about 9:30 on 2/18/13, i walked out of my garage heading toward my backyard (west) and was startled by 2 unusually bright orange flame-like lights in the sky one above and slightly to the north of the other, probably about 50 degrees above the horizon.  we are in the flight path of sky harbor airport so i am accustomed to seeing alot of airplane lights and helicopter lights and these were unlike anything i had seen before.  i also saw the "phoenix lights" years ago and these were unlike those either.  they appeared to be just hovering, i don't believe they were very close to me so it is difficult to judge how large they were. the most striking aspect of these objects was the color - they truly looked like two firey balls in the sky.  they hovered for about 3 minutes and the higher light began to fade out.  i ran inside to get my cell phone and by the time i came back out the higher object had completely faded away and the other was fading fast and i was not able to get a pic before it disappeared. the entire incident probably lasted only 5 minutes, from the time i first saw them, but they could have been up there for awhile before i went outside and saw them.
content.summary: Walked out of the house at about 9:30 turned and looked west  and saw two bright orange lights which hovered for a while and then faded away.

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were traveling in our car and it was such a beautiful day without a cloud in the sky...The sun was so bright that we wasn't trying to look at the sky at all and i was even contemplating putting on my shades to block the sun. fortunate for me, i looked up and noticed that a plane coming from the west was flying extremely high but, what captivated my attention was that a star seemed like it was inside our atmosphere and even as low as a cloud would appear..So i asked my wife, "do you see that"...So she starting noticing the same thing that i was, and was super amazed at the glowing object that looked like it was a diamond shaped chrome object that was shining so bright as if it had its own light illuminating from itself that it was amazing! we watched for at least 2 mins and my wife decided to get out her camera phone and as she was about to record it, it disappeared as if it teleported or something...Simply amazing! i'm definetely a firm believer that other beings exist outside of this world...And the technology they have is simply unbelievable to our kind that it baffled us that we actually seen this!
content.summary: Hovered for few mins and disappeared or took of so fast that we didn't see it leave

content.detailedDescription: I just got in my car and  was traveling west when i noticed a bright metallic object in the sky.  i looked at the clock right away and saw that it said 3:02 pm mtn  i watched the object for a few seconds then lost it in the sun. i drove back a bit to see if i could see it from where i first saw it but had not luck so i drove forward again and spotted it again further west. only watched it for a few more seconds and then it was gone.   the object was traveling sw when i first noticed it. as i said it was metallic in color and reflected the sun.  from where i saw it, it appeared to be cigar/ pencil shape.  i do not know how far off it was  but if i was to hold a silver pen up to my face that would be about what i saw.  i have tried to contact the local airport and have not gotten hold of anyone. i have also called the sheriffs office and no one else had reported anything at the time. the object was just below the sun.  later in the day i watched a prop plane and a jet take off. they both made sound even after i could not see them anymore. this object made no sound.
content.summary: Noticed shiny object in sky

content.detailedDescription:
A friend and i were on the way home on hwy 259 headed north. as we came over the hill prior to the bridge over lone star lake, we saw straight ahead an red orange glow in the sky just above the clouds. this was a huge glow. our first thought was a house fire or something of the sort. so we immediately turned off the highway and drove towards the light, only the further we drove west to it the farther west it would get from us. about 15 min later it just whooshed up and away into the clouds.

we were baffled by the experience and i still would like to know what it was over jenkins, texas.
